trapomino

Class Auxillary

  • java.lang.Object
    • trapomino.Auxillary

  • public class Auxillary
extends java.lang.Object
    This class reads the sprites into the game and assigns them to their coordinating game objects. This class will then return the proper image to any class that calls for use of a sprite by it's name. Finally, this class returns the shape of an Object on the Grid based on the Object's name.

      • Auxillary

        public Auxillary()
        This constructor reads all of the Images from the Graphics folder and assigns them to their relating names. If the program encounters an Exception during this process, it will write the error in the ErrorLogger file.

      • stringToShape

        public static Grid.SHAPE stringToShape(java.lang.String shape)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        the shape of a Block/Animal or no shape if the name has no corresponding Image
